refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public stringDirectoryIterator::getBasename stringsuffix""
Get the base name of the current DirectoryIterator item.

&reftitle.parameters;
suffix
If the base name ends in suffix, this will be cut.

  &reftitle.examples;



    A DirectoryIterator::getBasename example


     This example will list the full base name and the base name with 
     suffix .jpg removed for the files in the directory
     containing the script.



<?php
$dir = new DirectoryIterator(dirname(__FILE__));
foreach ($dir as $fileinfo) {
    if ($fileinfo->isFile()) {
        echo $fileinfo->getBasename() . "\n";
        echo $fileinfo->getBasename('.jpg') . "\n";
    }
}
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


